    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Study on Recruitment Analysis with Special Reference To 24x7 Corporate Solutions Pvt Ltd, Chennai</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Alexander.S.A</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Recruitment Analysis<br />Corporate Solutions</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5782</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">The entire project throws light on recruitment process followed by 24x7 Corporate Solution. The recruitment process is immediately followed by the selection process i.e. the final interviews and the decision making, conveying the decision and the appointment formalities. The key factor of the project is to analyze the recruitment sources followed by 24x7 Corporate Solution and to find out the process involved in these sources. The various interview techniques followed by 24x7 Corporate Solution and the process involved in these techniques will be thoroughly studied during the project period.
Multiple rounds of job interviews are conducted by the company to hire a candidate. The
selection procedure followed by the company will be analyzed which involves the process of
putting right men on right job. 24x7 Corporate Solution matches organizational requirements with the skills and qualifications of people during the selection process in this way. By selecting best candidate for the required job, the organization is getting quality performance of employees.
A questionnaire method will be followed to obtain the responses from the employees. Random sampling method will be used for research. To find out the correlation between various factors by using various tools like anova, Chi square test, Percentage analysis method. Based on this study, suggestions and recommendations will be given to the company for their betterment and for the companyâ€™s welfare.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/10656">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/10656</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/9711">MBA-2012</a><br/></td></tr>
